1
00:00:01,460 --> 00:00:22,730
That was fun. Traditional melody on a very unique instrument. That is a real ripsaw. Is that right? It's a seesaw. I saw that earlier and thought that is fantastic. You're going to hear more of that before the day is over. Praise the Lord. Welcome. We're glad that you're here.

2
00:00:23,270 --> 00:00:24,770
And Happy New Year to you all.

3
00:00:25,370 --> 00:00:28,910
It just seems like yesterday we were embracing 2002.

4
00:00:29,970 --> 00:00:33,130
It seems like yesterday, to me, we were just starting this new millennium.

5
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:35,560
And already it's 2003.

6
00:00:36,860 --> 00:00:43,300
And it's that time of year when we, for better or for worse, we look backward and we look forward.

7
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:47,700
We ask ourselves, what was 2002 all about?

8
00:00:48,780 --> 00:00:49,700
What went well?

9
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:52,930
What would we do differently?

10
00:00:54,590 --> 00:00:55,570
What would we change?

11
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:02,510
What are you going to do with the year in front of you?

12
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:05,090
I did some math.

13
00:01:05,370 --> 00:01:12,470
We all start off with the same 12 months, 52 weeks, 365 days.

14
00:01:14,160 --> 00:01:15,360
You want to know how it breaks out from there?

15
00:01:16,260 --> 00:01:19,040
8,760 hours.

16
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:22,390
That's what you get for 2003.

17
00:01:23,290 --> 00:01:26,810
525,600 minutes, if you want to look at it that way.

18
00:01:26,810 --> 00:01:33,530
or 31,536,000 seconds coming up in front of us.

19
00:01:33,530 --> 00:01:37,950
How will you use your time this year?

20
00:01:38,990 --> 00:01:45,730
Well, I like some New Year's resolutions that were posted on a newspaper back east.

21
00:01:45,810 --> 00:01:47,130
I'll share them with you this morning.

22
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:52,800
As people talked about thinking about the future, these are real New Year's resolutions.

23
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:59,300
The first is, I resolve to stop feeding the office plant leftover coffee.

24
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,180
I will use water instead.

25
00:02:03,780 --> 00:02:07,940
I don't know what all that issue is that's there, but that's a real one for somebody.

26
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:15,260
Somebody else said, my New Year's resolution is to really start collecting Muppet and peanut stuff in the coming year.

27
00:02:17,870 --> 00:02:18,450
I don't know.

28
00:02:20,190 --> 00:02:25,810
Third one, much as I hate government intervention, I resolve to try and get a law passed

29
00:02:25,810 --> 00:02:28,930
that requires every person on the face of the earth

30
00:02:28,930 --> 00:02:32,570
to use their common sense at least once a day.

31
00:02:34,670 --> 00:02:35,730
Thought that was appropriate.

32
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:38,160
I like this one.

33
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:42,800
As a theater major, I seldom have time to eat real food,

34
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,240
never mind eating with my family.

35
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:49,400
This year, I resolve to try really hard

36
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,420
to stop eating McDonald's and Wendy's

37
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:52,920
for two out of three meals a day.

38
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,820
If that isn't possible,

39
00:02:54,820 --> 00:02:58,500
I promise to at least clean the remains from my car.

40
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:02,600
I hope that didn't mean eating the remains.

41
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,360
I wasn't sure, but I don't think so.

42
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:09,580
I wish to become the old crone that my body already says that I am

43
00:03:09,580 --> 00:03:12,680
and stop trying to look like Barbie due to our culture.

44
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,110
Three more.

45
00:03:16,190 --> 00:03:19,430
I hereby resolve to accept the changes occurring at work.

46
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:23,170
I will try to remember that the decision makers have a brain

47
00:03:23,170 --> 00:03:24,990
and will use it if necessary.

48
00:03:25,490 --> 00:03:27,650
Finally, I will cheer them if it works

49
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:30,610
and will not laugh if it doesn't.

50
00:03:31,240 --> 00:03:31,860
Fair enough.

51
00:03:33,650 --> 00:03:35,370
Somebody else posted this on the web.

52
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:39,130
I refuse to take responsibility for my actions and decisions,

53
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:42,570
to never take the blame, to not stand by my promises,

54
00:03:42,930 --> 00:03:44,550
and to ignore the needs of the poor.

55
00:03:45,010 --> 00:03:47,330
In short, I will become a politician.

56
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:48,780
Harsh.

57
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,860
And finally, I like this one too.

58
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:56,420
To become as wonderful a person as my dog thinks that I am.

59
00:03:57,350 --> 00:03:58,110
There you go.

60
00:03:58,110 --> 00:04:06,120
When you think about it, New Year's resolutions are basically items that fall into three categories.

61
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:09,500
And they deal with essentially these three issues.

62
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:14,780
Things to make us live longer and to look better, that would be one.

63
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:20,140
Or things to help us have more of whatever it is we want.

64
00:04:20,700 --> 00:04:25,660
Or finally, things that help us to get along better with others.

65
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,220
Three different categories.

66
00:04:28,220 --> 00:04:34,930
We could call them longevity, prosperity, and peace.

67
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:41,370
And I think deep down we all desire those things to some degree in some form.

68
00:04:41,670 --> 00:04:46,870
And there are right ways about going after those things, and there are wrong ways to do so.

69
00:04:47,610 --> 00:04:52,890
God's Word gives us guidance in how to pursue those things.

70
00:04:53,890 --> 00:04:59,950
And so this morning, I'd like for us to think in terms of some New Year's resolutions.

71
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:09,750
If you have not made any, I've got ten this morning from the scripture that I believe is really going to impact and change your life.

72
00:05:10,910 --> 00:05:14,210
And I want to say to those who are here perhaps for the first time,

73
00:05:14,590 --> 00:05:22,510
and if you're looking for a coherent, consistent way to order your life and find meaning in your life,

74
00:05:23,560 --> 00:05:29,860
The Bible is the place where you can find that kind of structure and meaning and purpose.

75
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:33,000
And I'd like for you to explore this morning with us.

76
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:36,360
As we look at a chapter you may not have looked at for a while,

77
00:05:36,360 --> 00:05:46,300
but Proverbs chapter 3, in terms of pursuing longevity, prosperity, and peace done God's way.

78
00:05:48,530 --> 00:05:53,070
And so I begin this morning with the prologue to this chapter, chapter 3 of Proverbs.

79
00:05:53,070 --> 00:05:55,310
And the author says this,

80
00:05:56,070 --> 00:06:00,750
My child, never forget the things that I have taught you.

81
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:07,540
Store my commands in your heart, for they will give you a long and satisfying life.

82
00:06:08,300 --> 00:06:11,360
We desire a long and satisfying life.

83
00:06:12,390 --> 00:06:16,490
Therefore, let us take these teachings and embed them in our hearts.

84
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:23,570
Now, I want to say this, that wisdom sayings from Scripture are primarily wisdom sayings.

85
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:28,150
They are not direct promises that you can hold on to and say,

86
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:33,570
God, if I did what you said would happen and it doesn't happen, I'll hold you to it.

87
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:39,800
Wisdom sayings are wisdom that give us general directions in life.

88
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:42,350
Do you see the difference?

89
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:44,710
I want us to be careful as we interpret these.

90
00:06:44,710 --> 00:06:47,050
But they do set us on a course.

91
00:06:47,450 --> 00:06:49,530
that is healthy and helpful.

92
00:06:50,490 --> 00:06:51,490
And so here it begins.

93
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,930
Proverbs 3, 3 and 4.

94
00:06:56,460 --> 00:07:01,040
Never let loyalty and kindness get away from you.

95
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:03,280
Wear them like a necklace.

96
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:05,740
Write them deep within your heart.

97
00:07:06,700 --> 00:07:09,840
Then you will find favor with both God and people,

98
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:12,300
and you will gain a good reputation.

99
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:14,880
So what can we resolve?

100
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:17,730
Resolution number one, be it resolved.

101
00:07:17,730 --> 00:07:26,410
I resolve, too, and I hope you'll join me in this, to never let love and faithfulness leave me throughout this year.

102
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:31,870
I will be committed to love and faithfulness.

103
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:42,370
If you want to be a blessing and receive blessing, all you have to do is live out of love and faithfulness in your life.

104
00:07:44,830 --> 00:07:47,590
You know the people who want the best for someone else.

105
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:49,790
and before they want it from themselves.

106
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:52,990
Those are the kind of people who live out of love.

107
00:07:53,210 --> 00:07:57,470
They put others first, people who do what they say

108
00:07:57,470 --> 00:08:00,290
and stick close by through thick and thin.

109
00:08:00,290 --> 00:08:02,890
Those people are faithful people.

110
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:08,490
Faithfulness is a wonderful quality to have and to live out.

111
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:13,070
And friends, when you bless others by living from those core foundations,

112
00:08:13,550 --> 00:08:16,070
others can't help but be blessed by you.

113
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:22,610
and what happens is this over time you develop strong relationship with other people and when

114
00:08:22,610 --> 00:08:28,070
you do you begin to experience the rich blessing and the kind of prosperity that riches and fame

115
00:08:28,070 --> 00:08:38,020
cannot touch so how do you live out of love and faithfulness i believe you soak those up

116
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:45,360
soak them up like a sponge from the holy spirit you cultivate a life of faithfulness in seeking

117
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:53,500
from the holy spirit and allowing him to permeate your life the image from the scripture is about

118
00:08:53,500 --> 00:09:00,610
wearing those qualities around your neck as a necklace it's intentional it's having them with

119
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:09,740
you at all times god blesses a life of faithfulness and love and i find that you will find that as you

120
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:16,150
do that your relationships with others and with god will deepen and become more meaningful so

121
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:19,090
Number one, live out of love and faithfulness.

122
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:23,340
Number two, trust in the Lord with all your heart.

123
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:25,720
Do not depend on your own understanding.

124
00:09:26,320 --> 00:09:31,460
Seek His will in all that you do, and He will direct your paths.

125
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:38,420
I resolve to, number two, to trust in the Lord this year with all of my heart.

126
00:09:39,410 --> 00:09:40,210
Will you?

127
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:44,800
I want my life to count for the Lord.

128
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:50,340
I want it to count for the Lord and not just what people say.

129
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:52,380
is worthy or valuable.

130
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:56,040
I want a life that is morally honoring to the Lord.

131
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,440
I want my life to have God's imprint all over it.

132
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:02,340
And I know that's your desire as well.

133
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:05,480
For some of you this year,

134
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,340
you may have to make some big decisions

135
00:10:08,340 --> 00:10:13,020
about jobs and family and moral dilemmas

136
00:10:13,020 --> 00:10:14,200
and all kinds of things.

137
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:16,100
Will you make those decisions

138
00:10:16,100 --> 00:10:19,000
based on your own understanding,

139
00:10:19,180 --> 00:10:20,000
your own desires?

140
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:25,040
Will you make them based on God's truth as revealed in the Scriptures?

141
00:10:26,330 --> 00:10:30,180
What will be your basis as you chart your course this year?

142
00:10:31,680 --> 00:10:33,780
Trust in the Lord with all of your heart.

143
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:37,760
May it be resolved that that's one of our resolutions for our year.

144
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:42,310
Proverbs 3, verse 7 and 8.

145
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,660
Don't be impressed with your own wisdom.

146
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:50,460
Instead, fear the Lord and turn your back on evil.

147
00:10:51,330 --> 00:10:54,590
Then you will gain renewed health and vitality.

148
00:10:56,040 --> 00:11:01,090
Resolution number three, I resolve to be not wise in my own eyes.

149
00:11:01,430 --> 00:11:09,580
In our contemporary world, we have access to so much information.

150
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:12,730
My wife is a whiz at this.

151
00:11:13,230 --> 00:11:17,570
She can sit down in five minutes, tap into any network anywhere around the world,

152
00:11:17,730 --> 00:11:21,010
and produce information on any topic just like that.

153
00:11:21,090 --> 00:11:23,270
She's more intuitive at it than I am.

154
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:26,850
We can get wisdom and information at light speed.

155
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:31,310
And our culture also has this habit of thinking that we,

156
00:11:31,650 --> 00:11:33,850
with all of our wisdom and knowledge and understanding,

157
00:11:34,190 --> 00:11:37,250
have the right to determine how we're going to live morally.

158
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,620
But God's Word says to ultimately trust in the Lord,

159
00:11:42,490 --> 00:11:44,950
to have a healthy fear and respect for God.

160
00:11:46,370 --> 00:11:51,570
Our own wisdom, our own understanding is still tainted and biased by sin

161
00:11:51,570 --> 00:11:53,050
and by our own limited perspective.

162
00:11:53,050 --> 00:11:59,460
I believe our knowledge and our wisdom and our understanding of things in the world has great value.

163
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:03,100
But God's perspective must supersede them all.

164
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:08,980
And we must turn our backs on evil, even when it seems right sometimes.

165
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:13,300
Even in the world's eyes, whatever is laid before us may seem right.

166
00:12:13,940 --> 00:12:17,020
In God's eyes, it might still be tainted with evil.

167
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:19,320
Can we turn our back on those things?

168
00:12:21,230 --> 00:12:23,590
Can we be not wise in our own eyes?

169
00:12:26,130 --> 00:12:28,070
Proverbs 3, verse 9.

170
00:12:28,330 --> 00:12:35,060
Honor the Lord with your wealth and with the best part of everything your land produces.

171
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:41,700
Then He will fill your barns with grain and your vats will overflow with the finest of wine.

172
00:12:42,630 --> 00:12:48,250
Resolution number four for 2003, I resolve to honor the Lord with my wealth.

173
00:12:50,700 --> 00:12:52,220
Do we take that seriously today?

174
00:12:53,830 --> 00:12:57,030
All of life, all of life is stewardship.

175
00:12:57,030 --> 00:13:02,530
What will you do with your money, your possessions, your talents, your time?

176
00:13:03,010 --> 00:13:04,530
It is a stewardship issue.

177
00:13:05,170 --> 00:13:07,070
God has given us all these things.

178
00:13:07,410 --> 00:13:11,750
Will you be faithful to God as He has been faithful to you?

179
00:13:13,310 --> 00:13:19,100
As we talked about last year, throughout the Bible, this theme comes up over and over.

180
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:22,900
Blessings for obedience, curses for disobedience.

181
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,460
We joked about that.

182
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:26,820
Blessings and curses, which do you choose?

183
00:13:26,820 --> 00:13:33,720
obedience blessings disobedience curses it goes on and on throughout the scriptures and once again

184
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:40,010
this passage is part of that overarching theme if you want all that god has for you

185
00:13:40,010 --> 00:13:47,680
faithful stewardship and honoring the lord with your wealth is a part of that and i want to say

186
00:13:47,680 --> 00:13:54,360
this in addition friends can you imagine where this church could go in ministry if we were all

187
00:13:54,360 --> 00:14:01,140
obedient and faithful in honoring the lord with our wealth in this coming year if we all got really

188
00:14:01,140 --> 00:14:08,400
serious and really committed to saying lord i give you a tenth of what you give to me as an

189
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:14,620
offering back to you can you imagine the kind of income we could use for ministry here and around

190
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:22,690
the world it boggles my mind i look forward to seeing god do that through us let's be faithful

191
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:25,250
and make that a resolution for our year.

192
00:14:26,340 --> 00:14:28,860
And I know you're sitting there and you're saying,

193
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:30,980
you don't know my financial situation.

194
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:35,660
My wife and I laid last night in bed staring at the ceiling for a few moments

195
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:38,160
thinking through new decisions about our own finances.

196
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:40,780
And friends, I know it's hard.

197
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:43,980
It is hard to make those kinds of decisions.

198
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:47,200
They have impact that goes so far in our lives.

199
00:14:48,530 --> 00:14:52,330
I want us to be faithful as God calls us to be faithful

200
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:55,750
and allow him to bless as we do so.

201
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,950
Those are real decisions, and they're good ones.

202
00:15:00,490 --> 00:15:03,390
They're hard ones, but they're the right ones.

203
00:15:03,390 --> 00:15:13,550
Number five, my child, don't ignore it when the Lord disciplines you,

204
00:15:14,470 --> 00:15:17,130
and don't be discouraged when he corrects you,

205
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:20,240
for the Lord corrects those he loves

206
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:23,760
as a father corrects a child in whom he delights.

207
00:15:25,160 --> 00:15:29,260
Resolution number five, I resolve to embrace the Lord's discipline.

208
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:35,380
Good parents, you know that we have to discipline our children.

209
00:15:36,830 --> 00:15:39,680
If we don't, we're in trouble.

210
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:42,650
Children need discipline.

211
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:46,130
Adults sometimes need discipline.

212
00:15:46,950 --> 00:15:48,910
It's not about being mean or nasty.

213
00:15:48,910 --> 00:15:49,890
It's about correction.

214
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:52,190
It's about setting them on the right path.

215
00:15:52,190 --> 00:16:00,430
It leads to good decisions, to good directions, to good behavior, to good character.

216
00:16:01,890 --> 00:16:03,890
And God desires the same for us.

217
00:16:04,980 --> 00:16:10,140
And sometimes He uses discipline to sharpen us and sharpen our behavior and our character.

218
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:13,180
He wants us to be like Jesus Christ.

219
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:20,300
And sometimes God has to shave off the rough edges of our personalities, our behavior, or our thinking.

220
00:16:21,970 --> 00:16:26,980
And sometimes he'll do it through somebody else in the body of Christ.

221
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:30,980
I want to encourage you not to shrink back from those challenges.

222
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:34,620
Embrace them, for they are for your own good.

223
00:16:35,930 --> 00:16:38,790
Even just a couple days ago, I had a conversation with one of you,

224
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:40,750
and we were wrestling with some issues,

225
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:46,790
and you were able to gently and wonderfully challenge me and correct me

226
00:16:46,790 --> 00:16:48,610
and give me new insight.

227
00:16:49,990 --> 00:16:52,090
And at first I thought, well, what is this?

228
00:16:52,090 --> 00:16:56,310
and then I realize this is God speaking to me through somebody else.

229
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,320
And I thank them for that.

230
00:16:59,220 --> 00:17:00,560
I've grown through the experience.

231
00:17:01,490 --> 00:17:01,970
I'm better.

232
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:03,960
I think more clearly.

233
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,380
I see my mistake and I'm moving in a different direction.

234
00:17:08,080 --> 00:17:08,880
I appreciate that.

235
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:12,500
I think we need to always embrace discipline when it comes.

236
00:17:13,390 --> 00:17:15,650
For as God does that, he's doing it for our good.

237
00:17:16,450 --> 00:17:18,010
Let's embrace discipline from the Lord.

238
00:17:18,010 --> 00:17:27,740
